parameters: Prince Rex: Hmm, there's a strange feeling.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Is that so? It feels just
like a brave hero about to embark on an adventure.

Prince Rex: I don't think a hero would run away... Alicia-
san seems more suited for it than me.
Prince Rex: Honestly, I don't know where to look...

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Hehe, there's nothing
that suits my body.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Next, we will be heading
towards Oros. We'll take a detour to shake off any pursuers,
so please allow us to do so.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: It would be great if we
could successfully meet up with our comrades...
Prince Rex: Why do you go to such lengths for me?

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Prince Rex is the
rightful successor of the empire. The throne is not
something to be stolen, but something to be bestowed upon.
Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: That's why--

Prince Rex: Sorry, my question was poorly worded. I want to
know the reason why you personally joined the rescue
mission.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: I was a torturer in the
dark division.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Since the time of King
Agnos...

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Since King Agnos fell
ill, my workload as a torturer has increased significantly
compared to before.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Queen Caron used the
Imperial Dark Agents privately to obtain the necessary
information for herself.
Prince Rex: I want to apologize in place of my father.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: I do consider it a
necessary job to maintain the nation, but I couldn't forgive
Caron for using it for her own desires.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: I bet on Prince Rex. I
believe that you won't do something like Caron did.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: I risked my life
believing that you would become a compassionate and kind
king who would shine upon us like the sun.

Former Imperial Dark Agent Alicia: Those who have died also
wish for it. In order to repay them, I will definitely make
Prince Rex the king.

Alicia's words reminded him of his mother, Leucos. Become a
compassionate king - these words strongly resonated with
Rex, who had abandoned the idea of becoming a king.

There is someone who believes in my potential. It fills
Rex's heart. At the same time, in order to repay those
words, it is necessary for him to become a king.

It is a path far removed from tolerance, a path paved with
blood. It is uncertain whether there is truly a throne at
the end of the road paved with blood. Nevertheless, it is a
long road that must be advanced upon.

Rex's heart continued to waver. Should he fight or should he
run? Should he seek revenge or should he betray? Should he
be a tolerant person or a courageous one, or perhaps
something completely different...

Every time I think about it, the words of a monster come to
mind. You can become anything, even a king, as you wish.

And now, Rex stood at a crossroads. It was the place where
Rex, who had been avoiding hesitation, finally arrived at a
choice he couldn't escape from. A monster thrashing about
inside a cage, a monster screaming in agony. Monster.
Monster. Monster.

With the presence of Alicia, Pido's demands, and Claire's
voice, the cage in Rex's heart was completely shattered
along with the screams that crushed him. Rex had fully
regained his original self before being suppressed.

For the Imperial history, it was a return of the heir to the
throne, fraught with such danger of 'reclaiming'.
